fix: USGS magnitude takes priority in severity merge during dedup

When a GDACS earthquake merges with USGS data, the combined event kept
GDACS's potentially older magnitude instead of USGS's authoritative value.
This caused the watch floor to see stale severity data.

Now USGS magnitude overrides GDACS magnitude when a GDACS-primary event
merges with USGS data, since USGS is the authoritative earthquake source
and typically has more frequent magnitude revisions.

Test: test_usgs_magnitude_overrides_gdacs_when_merging validates the fix.

